1381	/* We take a cached value of the unix time in the global state because with
1382	 * virtual memory and aging there is to store the current time in objects at
1383	 * every object access, and accuracy is not needed. To access a global var is
1384	 * a lot faster than calling time(NULL).
1385	 *
1386	 * This function should be fast because it is called at every command execution
1387	 * in call(), so it is possible to decide if to update the daylight saving
1388	 * info or not using the 'update_daylight_info' argument. Normally we update
1389	 * such info only when calling this function from serverCron() but not when
1390	 * calling it from call(). */
1391	void updateCachedTime(int update_daylight_info) {
1392	    const long long us = ustime();
1393	    updateCachedTimeWithUs(update_daylight_info, us);
1394	}
