1907	 * expensive jemalloc fragmentation measurement that cronUpdateMemoryStats()
1908	 * already performs for its own purposes earlier in the same cron tick.
1909	 *
1910	 * Lifecycle (single-threaded by Redis's main-thread invariant):
1911	 *   - Producer: defragFragCachePut() — called from cronUpdateMemoryStats()
1912	 *     after its zmalloc_get_allocator_info() call. Records server.cronloops
1913	 *     at publish time alongside the (Lua-subtracted) values.
1914	 *   - Consumer: defragFragCacheTake() — called from computeDefragCycles().
1915	 *     Returns 1 only when the recorded cronloops matches server.cronloops
1916	 *     (same tick); returns 0 otherwise. No explicit invalidation needed —
1917	 *     both serverCron() and whileBlockedCron() advance server.cronloops at
1918	 *     entry, so any value published in a previous tick is automatically
1919	 *     stale on the next entry. */
